1
00:00:05,851 --> 00:00:08,601
Could you tell us about
November 7th, 1980?

2
00:00:08,604 --> 00:00:09,738
I remember everything.

3
00:00:10,539 --> 00:00:14,403
Will and Julie went riding
their bikes around 4:00.

4
00:00:14,405 --> 00:00:17,236
Supposed to go by a friend's
house, kid says he never saw 'em.

5
00:00:17,238 --> 00:00:18,444
What did you do?

6
00:00:18,446 --> 00:00:20,027
You're their mother, where were you?

7
00:00:20,029 --> 00:00:21,444
I am entitled to a life!

8
00:00:21,446 --> 00:00:23,111
How long have you folks
been sleeping separate?

9
00:00:23,113 --> 00:00:25,640
Dan left last May,
then I took the couch.

10
00:00:25,643 --> 00:00:27,238
- Dan?
- My cousin.

11
00:00:27,701 --> 00:00:29,823
You're having memory problems, right?

12
00:00:29,826 --> 00:00:31,074
What?

13
00:00:31,077 --> 00:00:32,341
You have memory problems.

14
00:00:32,343 --> 00:00:34,695
Henry's coming with
the people from the TV.

15
00:00:34,697 --> 00:00:36,469
So, you caught the case back in '80?

16
00:00:36,471 --> 00:00:37,927
Didn't work again 'til 90.

17
00:00:37,930 --> 00:00:38,957
And your wife's book

18
00:00:38,959 --> 00:00:41,429
was considered a classic
of literary non-fiction.

19
00:00:41,432 --> 00:00:43,888
I teach English. Will's
a student of mine.

20
00:00:43,891 --> 00:00:45,903
There's a few of the older boys.

21
00:00:45,905 --> 00:00:47,861
They make it hard on the others.

22
00:00:47,863 --> 00:00:49,486
Last name is Woodard,

23
00:00:49,488 --> 00:00:51,778
saw him riding around when
I was looking for the kids.

24
00:00:51,780 --> 00:00:52,945
What's your partner doing?

25
00:00:52,947 --> 00:00:55,613
Man was a long-range
reconnaissance in 'Nam.

26
00:00:56,780 --> 00:00:59,528
I found the boy. There's
no sign of the girl.

27
00:00:59,530 --> 00:01:01,328
Two months ago, the burglary

28
00:01:01,331 --> 00:01:02,867
and only one set of prints.

29
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:03,993
Julie Purcell.

30
00:01:03,996 --> 00:01:05,113
She's alive?

31
