32
00:03:26,196 --> 00:03:29,986
You have the autopsy report.

33
00:03:29,988 --> 00:03:32,446
I don't need to go over that.

34
00:03:34,446 --> 00:03:36,486
Blunt force trauma...

35
00:03:36,488 --> 00:03:38,738
and a cervical fracture.

36
00:03:39,905 --> 00:03:42,736
Somebody broke his neck.

37
00:03:42,738 --> 00:03:44,446
Brought him to that cave.

38
00:03:46,405 --> 00:03:48,446
Folded his hands, I guess.

39
00:03:51,113 --> 00:03:52,820
Alan.

40
00:03:52,822 --> 00:03:55,027
Talk to me about
Oklahoma. You have to, man.

41
00:03:55,029 --> 00:03:56,609
Wayne, this isn't the time...

42
00:03:56,612 --> 00:03:58,777
How many sets of prints were taken?

43
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:02,109
Do they know she was one of
the robbers and not a customer?

44
00:04:02,112 --> 00:04:04,818
If they found her, you wouldn't
even be talkin' to me, right?

45
00:04:04,821 --> 00:04:06,361
Do they have video surveillance?

46
00:04:06,364 --> 00:04:08,289
Mr. Hays, the purpose of this deposition

47
00:04:08,292 --> 00:04:10,903
is to give your statement,
not to extract one from us.

48
00:04:10,905 --> 00:04:14,528
I'm pretty easygoin',
but go away already.

49
00:04:14,530 --> 00:04:16,861
I don't think I will.

50
00:04:16,863 --> 00:04:19,453
Look, we're not at
liberty to divulge details

51
00:04:19,456 --> 00:04:21,902
of an ongoing police investigation,

52
00:04:21,905 --> 00:04:24,152
nor to share discovery items with anyone

53
00:04:24,154 --> 00:04:25,861
other than the prosecutor's office.

54
00:04:25,863 --> 00:04:27,653
Now, you can talk to them,
if they'll talk to you...

55
00:04:27,655 --> 00:04:31,236
All right, stop.

56
00:04:31,238 --> 00:04:32,444
Wayne.

57
00:04:32,446 --> 00:04:35,653
Finish up today, all right?

58
00:04:35,655 --> 00:04:38,319
Then after, we'll speak.

59
00:04:38,321 --> 00:04:40,523
I'm sayin'...

60
00:04:40,526 --> 00:04:42,942
we'll talk. Okay?

61
00:04:46,071 --> 00:04:48,528
Now, you were sayin'.

62
00:04:48,530 --> 00:04:50,820
You questioned people during this time.

63
00:04:50,823 --> 00:04:54,364
- Right?
- Do you know another way to do it?

64
00:04:56,655 --> 00:04:58,820
The father worked at Wilson Body Works,

65
00:04:58,822 --> 00:05:01,027
where they used to make
parts for school buses.

66
00:05:01,029 --> 00:05:03,152
We talked to everybody there.

67
00:05:03,154 --> 00:05:06,361
Employed about a hundred
people from West Finger.

68
00:05:06,363 --> 00:05:08,695
The dolls were their own thing.

69
00:05:08,697 --> 00:05:11,321
Wasn't gettin' us anywhere, either.

70
00:05:18,530 --> 00:05:20,611
Thank you very much.

71
00:05:20,613 --> 00:05:23,486
That guy collected garbage, Woodard.

72
00:05:23,488 --> 00:05:25,069
We talked to him too.

73
00:05:25,071 --> 00:05:29,194
I saw the kids. They were
pedaling into the sun.

74
00:05:29,196 --> 00:05:30,947
Headed west?

75
00:05:32,863 --> 00:05:35,945
We went by your place.

76
00:05:35,947 --> 00:05:38,069
You sorta collect things, huh?

77
00:05:38,071 --> 00:05:40,403
I salvage trash that I can sell.

78
00:05:40,405 --> 00:05:42,569
You don't need to make
it sound better than that.

79
00:05:42,571 --> 00:05:46,444
You got any other properties?
Anywhere you keep things?

80
00:05:46,446 --> 00:05:49,069
I don't have anyplace else.

81
00:05:49,071 --> 00:05:51,569
What'd you do before this?

82
00:05:51,571 --> 00:05:54,486
Before you collected scrap.

83
00:05:54,488 --> 00:05:58,986
Uh, came back from overseas. '72.

84
00:05:58,988 --> 00:06:01,194
Did some carpentry.

85
00:06:01,196 --> 00:06:03,736
Construction dropped off.
Things didn't work out.

86
00:06:03,738 --> 00:06:06,611
My marriage. Stuff.

87
00:06:06,613 --> 00:06:08,569
I was gone too long.

88
00:06:08,571 --> 00:06:11,361
About four years ago she left me.

89
00:06:11,363 --> 00:06:13,279
Took the kids.

90
00:06:14,571 --> 00:06:16,569
I was motor pool.

91
00:06:16,571 --> 00:06:20,403
My man here was a LRRP. Two tours.

92
00:06:20,405 --> 00:06:24,655
Detective Hays. They called
him Purple Hays over there.

93
00:06:26,279 --> 00:06:28,027
You miss your family?

94
00:06:28,029 --> 00:06:30,903
I... Yeah.

95
00:06:30,905 --> 00:06:33,444
I miss being someone that way...

96
00:06:33,446 --> 00:06:35,405
a way I could have a family.

97
00:06:36,488 --> 00:06:38,277
You were recon?

98
00:06:38,279 --> 00:06:41,903
Seventy-fifth Infantry.

99
00:06:41,905 --> 00:06:44,152
Sergeant.

100
00:06:44,154 --> 00:06:46,194
You must be pretty insane.

101
00:06:46,196 --> 00:06:47,736
Volunteerin' for that.

102
00:06:47,738 --> 00:06:50,279
I didn't think about it
much, tell ya the truth.

103
00:06:54,321 --> 00:06:56,111
I ain't one of them burnouts.

104
00:06:56,113 --> 00:07:00,179
Ya know, comes back bustin'
guys up, gettin' high.

105
00:07:00,182 --> 00:07:01,903
And I ain't a bum.

106
00:07:01,905 --> 00:07:04,319
I keep a house. I pay my way!

107
00:07:04,321 --> 00:07:06,822
Hey. I ain't judgin', man.

108
00:07:08,154 --> 00:07:11,778
Look, I punch in and out.

109
00:07:11,780 --> 00:07:13,861
I put on a suit in the mornin'.

110
00:07:13,863 --> 00:07:16,027
And bein' honest...

111
00:07:16,029 --> 00:07:19,446
I don't have much of a life.

112
00:07:20,488 --> 00:07:22,528
So why?

113
00:07:22,530 --> 00:07:24,403
Why punch in?

114
00:07:24,405 --> 00:07:26,903
Why the suit? Why...

115
00:07:26,905 --> 00:07:29,571
I don't ask myself questions like that.

116
00:07:31,071 --> 00:07:34,154
Could be I'm too
chickenshit, Mr. Woodard.

117
00:07:36,530 --> 00:07:38,695
It ain't my world.

118
00:07:38,697 --> 00:07:41,277
Less than yours, even.

119
00:07:41,279 --> 00:07:44,029
But I did pretty good
at following orders.

120
00:07:45,363 --> 00:07:47,319
Now...

121
00:07:47,321 --> 00:07:49,632
You ever do this?

122
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:52,008
I miss when "Don't get killed"

123
00:07:52,019 --> 00:07:54,810
was the only thing on my to-do list.

124
00:07:56,321 --> 00:07:59,820
It's hard to unplug from that.

125
00:07:59,822 --> 00:08:02,321
I spent a year comin' down.

126
00:08:06,655 --> 00:08:10,405
Just to go back over it, you
sure you didn't see anything?

127
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:12,945
I told you.

128
00:08:12,947 --> 00:08:15,361
I saw the teenagers out there, too.

129
00:08:15,363 --> 00:08:17,903
I was goin' in the other direction.

130
00:08:17,912 --> 00:08:20,370
You like kids, generally?

131
00:08:21,691 --> 00:08:23,439
Do...

132
00:08:23,442 --> 00:08:25,942
What the fuck's the
right answer to that?

133
00:08:28,787 --> 00:08:30,110
You think I...

134
00:08:30,113 --> 00:08:33,569
Listen, I got two kids, okay?

135
00:08:33,571 --> 00:08:35,238
Where are they?

136
00:08:36,363 --> 00:08:38,111
I don't know.

137
00:08:38,113 --> 00:08:40,027
She didn't tell me.

138
00:08:40,029 --> 00:08:42,361
And I haven't gone lookin'.

139
00:08:42,363 --> 00:08:45,569
If I'd never left...

140
00:08:45,571 --> 00:08:48,029
I think it'd have been fine.

141
00:08:49,071 --> 00:08:52,569
But to go, and come back...

142
00:08:52,571 --> 00:08:55,778
I just couldn't put myself back
in that old story, that's all.

143
00:08:55,780 --> 00:08:58,988
And I couldn't leave
it, either. Ya know?

144
00:09:00,780 --> 00:09:03,945
You ever been someplace
you couldn't leave,

145
00:09:03,947 --> 00:09:06,695
and you couldn't stay...

146
00:09:06,697 --> 00:09:09,571
both at the same time?

147
00:09:17,613 --> 00:09:19,446
Do you remember the place?

148
00:09:25,196 --> 00:09:26,905
I remember.

149
00:09:37,738 --> 00:09:41,277
I can tell you all that
none of us will rest

150
00:09:41,279 --> 00:09:43,528
until we achieve justice in the matter.

151
00:09:43,530 --> 00:09:45,820
Our detectives are hard at work,

152
00:09:45,822 --> 00:09:49,194
and this is priority
one for law enforcement

153
00:09:49,196 --> 00:09:52,903
in Washington County
and Northwest Arkansas.

154
00:09:52,905 --> 00:09:54,720
Now, it's temporary,

155
00:09:54,723 --> 00:09:57,116
but we're gonna have to have
a curfew for a little while.

156
00:09:57,119 --> 00:09:59,630
It's important that we keep
an eye on our kids right now,

157
00:09:59,633 --> 00:10:02,129
and we want to make sure you
know where they are at all times,

158
00:10:02,132 --> 00:10:05,486
and that they're indoors by 8:00.

159
00:10:05,488 --> 00:10:09,027
Now, we can't really say too
much about the investigation,

160
00:10:09,029 --> 00:10:11,486
but I'm here to answer
any questions I can.

161
00:10:11,488 --> 00:10:14,361
Well, I don't let mine
go near Devil's Den.

162
00:10:14,363 --> 00:10:16,945
Everybody knows you got
something happenin' in it.

163
00:10:16,947 --> 00:10:18,376
Bums, junkies.

164
00:10:18,379 --> 00:10:20,403
Queers meet up out there.

165
00:10:20,405 --> 00:10:22,653
You have a question, sir?

166
00:10:22,655 --> 00:10:24,945
I wanna know what y'all are
doing to break up that stuff.

167
00:10:24,947 --> 00:10:26,986
Clean up that park!

168
00:10:26,988 --> 00:10:28,444
What about these junkies?

169
00:10:28,446 --> 00:10:30,861
You got heroin in Arkansas now.

170
00:10:30,863 --> 00:10:34,069
Right now our focus is tryin'
to find this little girl

171
00:10:34,071 --> 00:10:35,528
and bring her home.

172
00:10:35,530 --> 00:10:37,695
We're considering every possibility.

173
00:10:37,697 --> 00:10:39,194
And what about that fella

174
00:10:39,196 --> 00:10:41,775
always diggin' through
everybody's trash?

175
00:10:41,778 --> 00:10:43,860
Mr. Kindt, can you tell us

176
00:10:43,863 --> 00:10:45,611
if they think the girl is still alive?

177
00:10:45,613 --> 00:10:47,861
It's our hope that she's alive, yes.

178
00:10:47,863 --> 00:10:51,725
But again, I really can't discuss any
of the details of the investigation.

179
00:10:51,728 --> 00:10:55,986
Now, our detectives have a
pair of Xeroxes to pass out.

180
00:10:55,988 --> 00:10:59,653
One is a picture of Julie Purcell.

181
00:10:59,655 --> 00:11:02,889
The other is the kind of
backpack that the boy, Will, had.

182
00:11:02,892 --> 00:11:05,111
It's red and has his name on it.

183
00:11:05,113 --> 00:11:08,361
Now, if anyone has any
information of potential interest,

184
00:11:08,363 --> 00:11:09,820
no matter how far afield,

185
00:11:09,822 --> 00:11:11,403
share it with us.

186
00:11:11,405 --> 00:11:14,319
And trust that we will not
let this terrible, cowardly act

187
00:11:14,321 --> 00:11:16,111
go unpunished.

188
00:11:16,113 --> 00:11:18,986
Your old boss got
real vocal around then.

189
00:11:18,988 --> 00:11:21,736
Gerald Kindt had an election
comin' up the next year.

190
00:11:21,738 --> 00:11:25,903
I know. I guess that works to
some point in your petition.

191
00:11:25,905 --> 00:11:29,113
It's worth notin', I
think, his motivations.

192
00:11:30,238 --> 00:11:31,653
Well...

193
00:11:31,662 --> 00:11:34,078
now he's fuckin' State Attorney General.

194
00:11:35,822 --> 00:11:38,790
But we didn't work for
him. He was your boss.

195
00:11:38,793 --> 00:11:41,113
Oh, not for a good while now.

196
00:11:44,154 --> 00:11:46,403
The broken neck is clear.

197
00:11:46,405 --> 00:11:48,277
But the way the arms were folded...

198
00:11:48,279 --> 00:11:50,405
- I know.
- And the other thing.

199
00:11:50,408 --> 00:11:52,259
The hell are those dolls for?

200
00:11:52,262 --> 00:11:55,610
Correct. Look familiar, some way.

201
00:11:55,613 --> 00:11:58,444
Like the kind of thing at country fairs.

202
00:11:58,446 --> 00:12:01,778
What do you get from
that crowd in there?

203
00:12:01,780 --> 00:12:03,903
They're worried.

204
00:12:08,029 --> 00:12:10,861
Could be thinkin' it
coulda been a neighbor.

205
00:12:10,863 --> 00:12:15,695
Had 'em sign in. Saw some
shifty eyes in there, but...

206
00:12:15,697 --> 00:12:17,905
may be my redneck radar.

207
00:12:18,824 --> 00:12:20,449
I don't know.

208
00:12:21,694 --> 00:12:23,277
Excuse me.

209
00:12:38,655 --> 00:12:40,488
- Hi.
- Hey.

210
00:12:42,780 --> 00:12:44,655
You found him, didn't you?

211
00:12:47,988 --> 00:12:50,403
You look like you haven't
slept in a couple days.

212
00:12:50,405 --> 00:12:53,822
Work to do. How's it at school?

213
00:12:55,321 --> 00:12:56,697
Sad.

214
00:12:57,988 --> 00:13:00,321
People are scared.

215
00:13:05,238 --> 00:13:07,319
Well...

216
00:13:07,321 --> 00:13:09,154
been askin' about this.

217
00:13:10,488 --> 00:13:12,528
We haven't gotten anything.

218
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:16,321
I don't know, you
knowin' the kids and such.

219
00:13:18,029 --> 00:13:20,695
You ever seen anything like this?

220
00:13:20,697 --> 00:13:23,069
Seen a kid with a doll like this?

221
00:13:23,071 --> 00:13:26,361
Uh, maybe. I don't know.

222
00:13:26,363 --> 00:13:29,321
Looks like something you'd find
in a craft store or something.

223
00:13:31,113 --> 00:13:34,697
I... I haven't seen any
of the kids with them.

224
00:13:36,284 --> 00:13:37,657
Can I keep this?

225
00:13:37,660 --> 00:13:39,860
Uh, sure.

226
00:13:39,863 --> 00:13:41,820
I'll ask around with the kids,

227
00:13:41,822 --> 00:13:43,947
maybe check with the other teachers.

228
00:13:43,950 --> 00:13:45,617
All right. Thanks.

229
00:13:48,530 --> 00:13:50,653
Uh...

230
00:13:50,655 --> 00:13:52,446
Amelia.

231
00:13:55,154 --> 00:13:57,738
- Okay, I gotta go.
- All right.

232
00:13:59,571 --> 00:14:01,196
Be safe.

233
00:14:06,697 --> 00:14:08,319
Now, this family...

234
00:14:08,321 --> 00:14:10,501
Haven't we spent 
enough time with this?

235
00:14:20,947 --> 00:14:22,530
It's helpin' me.

236
00:14:24,154 --> 00:14:26,361
Bringin' things back.

237
00:14:26,363 --> 00:14:28,238
How's that?

238
00:14:30,985 --> 00:14:32,694
Your mother.

239
00:14:34,378 --> 00:14:36,628
I, uh...

240
00:14:38,780 --> 00:14:41,695
I have trouble seein' her sometimes.

241
00:14:41,697 --> 00:14:44,653
Or, uh... I know who she is,

242
00:14:44,655 --> 00:14:47,947
but the parts of our lives, pieces...

243
00:14:49,571 --> 00:14:51,822
I can't picture 'em.

244
00:14:53,947 --> 00:14:56,653
You think Mom wants
you to keep doin' this?

245
00:14:56,655 --> 00:14:59,988
It's bringin' things 
back. Goin' over the case.

246
00:15:01,029 --> 00:15:02,736
I'm rememberin' things.

247
00:15:02,738 --> 00:15:05,446
My life. Your sister.

248
00:15:11,495 --> 00:15:14,286
You know when the last
time I saw Rebecca?

249
00:15:18,822 --> 00:15:20,822
Mom's funeral?

250
00:15:22,947 --> 00:15:26,697
I think you talked on the
phone a few months back.

251
00:15:40,405 --> 00:15:43,154
You sure you wanna keep
talkin' to the TV people?

252
00:15:46,446 --> 00:15:48,403
That woman, the director...

253
00:15:48,405 --> 00:15:51,319
I wanna know what she's after.

254
00:15:51,321 --> 00:15:53,945
What they might know now.

255
00:15:53,947 --> 00:15:57,820
She said she'd, uh, show
me somethin' next time.

256
00:15:57,822 --> 00:15:59,861
She's baitin' ya, Dad.

257
00:15:59,863 --> 00:16:03,196
Do you think she cares at
all about you or who did it?

258
00:16:05,238 --> 00:16:08,569
She just wants people
to watch her shitty show.

259
00:16:08,571 --> 00:16:11,653
And I think...

260
00:16:11,655 --> 00:16:14,277
